###   ENGLISH6   ###
BM_the_supreme_governor_english:0 "The Supreme Governor"
BM_the_supreme_governor_english_desc:0 "The Supreme Governor of the Church of England was first used as a title by Queen Elizabeth of England and Ireland. This title was used as a compromise between the pro-papal and pro-anglican factions in England. The Governor title both established her rule and dominion over the Anglican church, unlike the title of 'Head of Church', it doesn't challenge the rule of the Pope directly, as well as sementing her position as a woman. In addition to this, the highly pragmatic sense of Elizabeth and her successors left enough space for talented people to serve regardless of their religious uniformity. Those who didn't wish to conform to this pragmatism where free to seek their fortune elsewhere, like the New World."

