BM_tariffs_trading_rights_english_desc:0 "There is nothing in the world more lucrative than trade, and we intend to capitalize on it. With the expansion of global trade routes, especially with the Triangle Trade, merchants are starting to sell and buy their goods and wares less in line with national interests, and more according to personal profitability. To not let our imports overtake our exports, putting us in a position of current account deficit, we are going to heavily tax imported goods, whilst reducing tax on our exports. We will also tax our colonial possessions to utilise all our assets in our economical reach."

